It provides functionalities like adding, removing, and editing reminders with additional features such as strikethrough and date handling.

Developers can define reminders with custom dates, text fields, or even multi-line descriptions, making it highly adaptable for personal and professional use cases.

####1. Define a Parent Element

Define two parent elements: one for buttons and one for items where the data controls will be rendered:

```html
<div id=\"reminderButtons\"></div>
<div id=\"reminderItems\"></div>
```

####2. Draw a Data Control

Use the `dataJs.draw` function to create a control for managing reminders:

```javascript
var parent_buttons = $('#reminderButtons');
var parent_items = $('#reminderItems');

dataJs.draw(parent_buttons, parent_items, {
    id: 'reminder-123',
    caption: 'Add Reminder',
    trash_enabled: true,
    copy_enabled: false,
    strikethrough_enabled: true,
    calendar: true, // Enables date input
    buttons: [
        {
            code: '1',
            name: 'task',
            icon: 'calendar',
            title: 'Add a Task'
        },
        {
            code: '2',
            name: 'event',
            icon: 'clock',
            title: 'Add an Event'
        }
    ],
    items: []
});
```

####3. Allowing Date Field

Enable date input for reminders by setting the `calendar` property to `true`. This will render a date picker field in the form:

```javascript
dataJs.draw(parent_buttons, parent_items, {
    calendar: true
});
```

####4. Switching Input Field into a TextArea

If the reminders require multi-line descriptions, enable a `textarea` instead of a single-line input field by setting the `textarea` property to `true`:

```javascript
dataJs.draw(parent_buttons, parent_items, {
    textarea: true
});
```

This allows users to input detailed descriptions for their reminders using a text area.







